  Whats the deal with Lodizal?</span><hr size=1> hiya everyone = )<br>
<br>
ok .. gonna try my best to keep this civilized here.<br>
<br>
about 2 weeks ago some guildies and i hear that Lodi is up so we rush over to IC. another guild is there and claiming it as a camp, and they have it camped. after some discussion we decide that whoever agroes Lodi gets him. shortly after Lodi spawns close to the other guild and they engage and we back off, pull up a cozy iceberg and watch the fight.<br>
tonight i run my war to the bazaar and decide to port over to IC to see if Lodi is up. when i find him up, i holler it in /gu and we head over. when i get to Lodi, he had obviously been agroed cause he was way up near the tower, but as i get close to him i pause, check his hp's, full .. look around for anyone else, no one ..  and walk up to him as he's wandering around and he agroes me (didnt hit him or anything).<br>
so i start to run him back to the rest of the guild and we start in on him. during the fight, my war who was MT goes down (along with a druid i think). so our ranger kites him around while my war gets rezzed and loots his gear. after gear is looted the ranger yells something about people attacking Lodi and so we all run up to where our ranger was. sure enough, the people who had been there before and agroed him were on him again.<br>
well, long story short, we were too busy trying to figure out what they were doing in /ooc that they killed him.<br>
so my question is this ..<br>
is Lodi a camp?<br>
does Lodi go to the first people to agro him even if they wipe?<br>
does Lodi go to whoever can get the most dmg. in 1st to get the KS (as said guild suggested)?<br>
does Lodi still belong to a group or guild if they are kiting him?<br>
<br>
this is the 3rd or 4th story ive heard in the past couple of months concerning Lodi. is there any way to clear this up once and for all?<br>
<br>
i know Lodi prolly isnt considered a very important mob anymore. but still worthy of being clarified IMHO.<br>
<br>
<br>
Jaredd/Moogg<br>
Clan X<br>
The Rathe<br>
