<br>
No.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>does Lodi go to the first people to agro him even if they wipe?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Lodizal belongs to the first person/group with a force capable of killing him, that engages.  If they wipe .. then he's actually a free mob who is not being engaged.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>does Lodi go to whoever can get the most dmg. in 1st to get the KS (as said guild suggested)?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Refer to above response.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>does Lodi still belong to a group or guild if they are kiting him?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
No.  Kiting does not count as 'engaging' on the mob.<br>
<br>
Note:  There are no server rules set for the Lodizal spawn, it's been a subject brought up many times and there's basically a gentlemen's agreement to it, to handle it as any other race spawn I believe. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=35287">Aandiian</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
