why didn't the &quot;rest of the guild&quot; keep fighting Lodi, instead of stopping to watch the warrior loot his stuff?  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=arianrhodsidhe>Arianrhod Sidhe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>S4H - GL</span><br>  Posts: 163<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(12/11/02 3:09:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=383.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Whats the deal with Lodizal?</span><hr size=1> So far the determination of whether he's FFA or not at the moment seems to be player determined.  I'd be interested in hearing what a GM would say about it - not sarcasm, I'm genuinely interested.  It seems like if you inserted random_mob_01 in the place of Lodizal, it would have been a KS.  They had the ability to kill Lodizal, they just had a snafu in the beginning.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zahrimxealdabooboos>Zahrim Xealdabooboos</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.socal.rr.com/xariyl/images/kermit3.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 115<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(12/11/02 3:24:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=383.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.socal.rr.com/xariyl/images/kermit3.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Whats the deal with Lodizal?</span><hr size=1> GM's do not recognize &quot;camps&quot; never have, never will.  They define Kill Stealing as attacking an ALREADY engaged mob and out damageing those who had already begun attacking, thus stealing the kill.  As previously stated by others in this thread, Lozidal is a FFA mob, First group of people to engage have rights to the mob untill either IT or THEY are dead.  Kiting the mob prior to a group engagement is not a valid &quot;engagement&quot; in the eyes of the RTA, but unsure as to how a GM would view it.  <br>
<br>
